---
title: "FAQ — Slade Networks"
description: "Answers to common questions about pricing, timelines, equipment, and what to expect from a Slade Networks installation in the Finger Lakes, NY."
navActive: faq
---
{% extends "base.njk" %}

{% block pageStyles %}
  <style>
    .section { padding: 12px 0 60px }
    .ctaSection { padding: 0 0 72px }
  </style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="heroBadge">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/></svg>
          Common questions answered
        </div>
        <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <p class="subtext">
          Straightforward answers about pricing, what to expect, and how projects work.
        </p>

        <div class="callout">
          <div>
            <h2>Don't see your question?</h2>
            <p>Reach out directly — we're happy to help.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ctaButtons">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/contact/">Get in touch</a>
            <a class="btn" href="mailto:info@sladenetworks.com?subject=Slade%20Networks%20Question">Email us</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="wrap">

        <div class="faqGroup reveal">
          <p class="groupLabel">Before you start</p>
          <div class="faq">

            <details>
              <summary>
                How much does it cost?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Pricing depends on the scope — the size of the space, what's being installed, how much cabling is involved, and what equipment is needed. No two projects are the same, so there's no flat rate.
                <br><br>
                As a general range: a home Wi-Fi upgrade is on the lower end, while a full install with cameras, cabling, and switching costs more. Equipment and labor are always quoted together so there are no surprises.
                <br><br>
                The free consultation is how we arrive at a real number. After visiting the space, you'll receive a detailed, written quote before any work begins.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                Do you serve my area?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                We're based in Penn Yan and serve the Finger Lakes region — including Keuka Park, Hammondsport, Watkins Glen, Geneva, Canandaigua, Naples, Victor, and Auburn. If you're a bit outside that range, reach out anyway — travel is possible depending on the project.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                What happens during the free consultation?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                We visit your space, discuss what isn't working and what you'd like to improve, and put together a plan — what equipment is needed, where it should go, and what everything will cost. For Wi-Fi and cameras, we can model coverage before anything is installed. You'll walk away with a clear recommendation and a written quote.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                Do I need to buy equipment first?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                No. Equipment sourcing is part of the project — it's included in your quote. If you already have compatible gear, we'll evaluate it and use what makes sense.
              </div>
            </details>

          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faqGroup reveal">
          <p class="groupLabel">The install</p>
          <div class="faq">

            <details>
              <summary>
                Can you fix an existing setup, or only do new installs?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Both. Many projects start as upgrades or fixes — poor Wi-Fi coverage, unreliable cameras, a disorganized rack. We'll diagnose the issue and put together a clear plan to resolve it.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                How long does a project take?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                It depends on scope. Some jobs are completed in a single visit; larger installs may take a few days. You'll receive a realistic timeline during the consultation so there are no scheduling surprises.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                Why UniFi? What equipment do you use?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Most installs use UniFi by Ubiquiti. It brings Wi-Fi, cameras, switching, and phone systems into a single management dashboard — fewer apps, one consistent system, and simpler support over time. It's commercial-grade hardware designed to be updated and maintained for years.
              </div>
            </details>

          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faqGroup reveal">
          <p class="groupLabel">After the install</p>
          <div class="faq">

            <details>
              <summary>
                Do I keep full access to my own system?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Absolutely. You get admin access and a complete walkthrough at handoff. Your system is yours — nothing is locked behind our credentials.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                Is ongoing support required?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                No. Most projects are one-time installs with a clean handoff. Ongoing support plans are available for clients who want proactive monitoring, firmware management, and faster troubleshooting — but they're entirely optional.
              </div>
            </details>

            <details>
              <summary>
                How do I get help after the install?
                <span class="chev" aria-hidden="true">&#8964;</span>
              </summary>
              <div class="answer">
                Email <a href="mailto:support@sladenetworks.com">support@sladenetworks.com</a>. If remote access is configured on your system, many issues can be diagnosed and resolved without scheduling a site visit.
              </div>
            </details>

          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="ctaSection reveal">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="ctaInner">
          <div>
            <h2>Still have questions?</h2>
            <p>The fastest way to get answers is to schedule a free consultation. We'll cover everything specific to your space and situation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="ctaButtons">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/contact/">Book a consultation</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
{% endblock %}
